@page "/about"

<SeoHead Title="About Enigma | Evolving Puzzle Maze Game"
         Description="Learn what Enigma is, how map discovery works, and why the game blends evolving puzzle mazes, co-op play, and a player-driven map economy."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma game, puzzle maze game, about Enigma, maze discovery game" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">About</span>
        <h1>What Is Enigma?</h1>
        <p>Enigma is a puzzle maze game built around discovery. Players move through room-based mazes, solve evolving puzzles, complete runs solo or in co-op, and build collections of maps that can be kept, traded, or sold.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>What Makes Enigma Different</h2>
        <p>Enigma treats mazes as collectible game objects. A successful run can lead to a saved map with its own art, value, owner, founder, and history. That creates a loop that mixes puzzle-solving, exploration, and a player-driven marketplace.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Core Systems</h2>
        <h3>Single-Player Runs</h3>
        <p>Generated and saved mazes use room-specific puzzle locks, timed runs, and permanent loss if the player abandons the maze.</p>
        <h3>Co-op Sessions</h3>
        <p>Two players can create a shared expedition, synchronize room movement, solve puzzles together, and split rewards once the finish conditions are met.</p>
        <h3>Maps and Ownership</h3>
        <p>Maps have owners, founders, ratings, best times, and marketplace value. Ownership can transfer, but discovery remains tied to actual completion.</p>
    </section>

